  <p>Halfway through 2Q20, the proper health authorities decreed the construction sector as an "essential" activity for the country, thus gradually lifting the measures
    restricting the construction of housing in each state; a fact that will be positive for the Companies in the sector, since the housing inventory in progress will be
    able to be completed and, therefore, begin its titling process.</p>

  <p>Likewise, the housing institutes continue to safeguard the stability of the industry, through payment deferral mechanisms and new credit granting schemes for the
    acquisition of new housing, such as those of FOVISSSTE, which implemented the programs "FOVISSSTE for all", which contemplates the origination of more than 3,000
    credits in 2020, and "Your house is waiting for you", which will provide about 2,500 credits to government employees of the health sector for the purchase or construction
    of housing; among others.</p>

